lf-reporting in surveys. Especially when you consider the Lizardman&#x27;s Constant of 4% https:&#x2F;&#x2F;slatestarcodex.com&#x2F;2013&#x2F;04&#x2F;12&#x2F;noisy-poll-results-and... This article was written in 2013. The Internet has become a significantly more toxic place since then, and I would imagine the constant is closer to 15-20% these days. reply Tijdreiziger 3 hours ago | root | parent [–] &gt; […] I would imagine the constant is closer to 15-20% these days. On what basis? reply AlecSchueler 3 hours ago | root | parent | next [–] Don&#x27;t you know this is HN? A hand wave here is worth more than any methodical research. reply wafflemaker 3 hours ago | root | parent | prev | next [–] On basis of spending a lot of my teenage time browsing 4chan, I&#x27;d say it&#x27;s not 15%, but closer to 69% or even whole 420%. You just loose faith in humanity from spending too much time on the internet. reply AlecSchueler 3 hours ago | root | parent | next [–] So we&#x27;re writing off the methodologies of the entire field of psychology on the basis of numbers pulled out of your--on the basis of your gut feeling? reply Tijdreiziger 3 hours ago | root | parent | prev | next [–] I doubt 4chan is representative for the entire Internet. reply Sohcahtoa82 2 hours ago | root | parent | prev | next [–] Based on what I learned from this video: https:&#x2F;&#x2F;youtu.be&#x2F;r7l0Rq9E8MY?t=2 reply vntok 3 hours ago | root | parent | prev [–] An online survey administered via Survey Monkey, of course. reply Consider applying for YC's Fall 2025 batch! Applications are open till Aug 4 Guidelines | FAQ | Lists | API | Security | Legal | Apply to YC | Contact Search:|cefa9f8ad572627127f72ce8ebf93265|1750106223
